7. JAPANESE CALLIGRAPHY — POETIC TITLE & INVOCATION
At the very top‑centre of the map, floating in the sky above the continent, is a grand, vertical column of Japanese calligraphy in gyōsho script, using an ink of gold‑flecked crimson that shimmers like dragon’s blood. Directly below it, a tiny vermilion woodblock‑stamp English translation appears in delicate brackets:

万界の神獣 — 黎明の地の伝説
[Legendary Beasts of All Realms — Land of Dawn]

To the left and right, two smaller columns read:

竜が空を支配し、不死鳥が炎を纏う
