The Agelta Border (Southern Edge): The bottom‑right corner is the edge of the Agelta Drylands, the warm ochre dunes lapping against the city’s southern walls like a golden sea. The Emerald Road is visible as a thin, dashed jade line, bringing caravans of camels and traders to the city’s gates.

The Grand Spire (Heart of the City): Dominating the centre of Eruditio is the Grand Spire, the tallest tower in the Land of Dawn. It is rendered as a magnificent, tiered structure of brass and copper, its surface covered in intricate, embossed gearwork and glowing runic circuitry. At its peak, a colossal crystal of pure arcane energy levitates, surrounded by orbiting rings of bronze. Tiny arcs of purple lightning leap from the crystal to the rings.

The Airship Docks: Ringing the upper levels of the Grand Spire and spreading across floating stone platforms are the Airship Docks. Dozens of tiny, beautifully detailed airship silhouettes — some with brass hulls, others with canvas envelopes — float tethered to the docks, their propellers frozen mid‑spin. Tiny engineer silhouettes can be seen loading cargo.

The Gear Quarter (Industrial Heart): To the west of the Grand Spire, the Gear Quarter is a dense, steam‑filled district of forges, foundries, and workshops. It is rendered as a labyrinth of low, stout buildings with smoking chimneys, interlocked by moving gear‑bridges. Tiny X.Borg silhouettes — a figure with a massive mechanical arm — patrol the streets. The quarter glows with the warm, amber light of a thousand furnaces.

The Academy of Arcane Sciences: To the east of the Spire lies the Academy, a serene campus of elegant, domed buildings and open‑air lecture halls, rendered in pale gold and silver. The Fountain of Knowledge at its centre is a pool of glowing purple liquid, surrounded by tiny scholar silhouettes reading from holographic scrolls.

The Lightning Reactor: At the city’s southern edge, powering everything, is the Lightning Reactor. It is a massive, sphere‑shaped structure of copper and glass, from which constant, branching arcs of purple lightning strike the surrounding conductor towers. The lightning is rendered in precise, sharp, electric‑violet sumi strokes.

The Aqueducts & Steam Vents: Winding through the entire city are elegant, raised aqueducts of silver‑washed stone, carrying glowing cyan mana‑water. Steam vents release rhythmic puffs of pale grey mist, adding a gentle, living atmosphere.

