Generate a 16:9 horizontal image (1920×1080 pixels). The Lantis Mountains dominate the entire central vertical axis of the frame, stretching from the top edge to the bottom edge like the spine of a god. The western half of the canvas reveals the easternmost fringe of the Moniyan Empire: its fortified border abbeys, golden plains, and the sacred Monastery of Light’s distant glow. The eastern half plunges into the Barren Lands: the haunted foothills, the creeping shadow of Necrokeep’s influence, and the distant, faintly glowing scar of the Abyss. The entire map is presented as a sacred, warning cartographic scroll — as if drawn by the Radiant Order’s highest cartographer and then captured, half‑corrupted, by a scholar of Necrokeep. All major landmarks are labelled in elegant English cartographic script.

3. STYLE: NEO‑UKIYO‑E WITH SUMI‑E INK WASH (THE AESTHETIC OF THE DIVIDE)
The entire map is rendered in an uncompromising fusion of Neo‑Ukiyo‑e woodblock aesthetics and Zen Sumi‑e ink‑wash techniques, with a deliberate, dramatic split down the centre. The western (Moniyan) side is painted with warm, golden washes, precise cathedral‑like brushstrokes, and the soft, diffuse light of divine radiance. The eastern (Barren/Abyssal) side is rendered in cold, fractured charcoal washes, sharp, jagged dry‑brush strokes, and the sickly cyan under‑glow of corruption. The mountain peaks themselves are a battlefield of these two aesthetics: their western faces are bathed in gold, their eastern faces plunge into shadow. The parchment base transitions subtly from a warm, sun‑lit ivory on the left to a cold, storm‑grey washi on the right. Raised gold and silver lacquer are used extensively for the holy fortresses; tarnished silver and weeping black lacquer for the corrupted outposts. Every element is executed with 8K‑grade texture fidelity, feeling simultaneously like a revered holy map and a forbidden, sorrowful document.

4. THE NEO‑UKIYO‑E BORDER — THE SPLIT RELIQUARY
The map is enclosed in a single, breathtaking border that physically embodies the divide. The left half of the border is a radiant Moniyan reliquary — a continuous frieze of Gothic arches in raised gold leaf, interwoven with griffin feathers and tiny Radiant Order crosses. The right half is an Abyssal/Barren reliquary — a jagged frieze of thorned, black‑iron vines and weeping eyes in tarnished silver. The two halves meet at the top‑centre and bottom‑centre in a pair of dramatic, clashing compass medallions: at the top, a golden griffin and a shadow‑wyrm locked in eternal combat; at the bottom, a Moniyan sword crossed with a demonic scythe. The innermost edge is a single, profoundly evocative broken enso circle — the left side a smooth stroke of warm gold ink, the right side a fractured, bleeding stroke of charcoal‑black sumi, a meditation on the broken unity of the Land of Dawn.

5. THE LANDSCAPE — ZOOMED‑IN, HYPER‑DETAILED LANTIS MOUNTAINS & BORDER REALMS
The range and its environs are a breathtaking, heart‑wrenching tapestry of sanctity and sorrow.

The Great Spine – The Peaks of the Lantis: The central axis is a titanic wall of jagged peaks, rendered in towering, sharp dry‑brush strokes. The western faces of the mountains are illuminated by a glorious, golden‑white light, their snowcaps pristine and reflecting the divine glow. The eastern faces plunge into permanent, cold shadow, their snow stained grey, their cliffs weeping thin, black rivulets of corruption. Along the very spine, ancient, colossal Grock silhouettes — the stone guardians placed by the Empire ages ago — stand sentinel, their forms cracked but resolute.

The Radiant Threshold (Moniyan Side): The left half of the canvas is the hallowed eastern frontier of the Moniyan Empire. The land is a series of rising, golden‑green foothills. The most prominent feature is the fortified monastery‑citadel of Sanctum Vigil, perched on a high plateau, its white‑stone towers and single, blazing gold spire acting as the first and greatest beacon against the darkness. Tiny knight silhouettes and supply wagons move along the winding Pilgrim’s Road that leads up to the main pass. In the far distance, the soft, divine glow of the Monastery of Light can be seen. Shimmering fields of golden wheat border the foothills, and the shapes of patrolling celestial griffins can be seen in the sky.

The Gate of Lament (The Main Pass): Cutting through the centre of the range is the primary land route to the east, the Gate of Lament. On the Moniyan side, it is a formidable, holy fortress‑gate of white and gold stone, carved with angels. On the Barren side, the gate is a ruined, haunted structure — the same fortress, but shattered and overgrown with weeping, black vines. The pass itself is a narrow, winding canyon, littered with the ancient debris of a thousand battles and the silhouettes of both Moniyan and demonic skeletons.

The Haunted Foothills (Barren Lands Side): The right half of the canvas descends into the Barren Lands. The foothills are a wasteland of ash‑grey ink, with jagged, petrified trees and winding, poisonous streams of black ichor. The distant, imposing silhouette of Necrokeep can be seen, its spires clawing at the sky. Tiny, ghostly wraith silhouettes drift through the valleys, and the watchful, burning eyes of a corrupted Shadow‑Grock can be seen in a deep canyon. A single, ruined watchtower — the Spire of Sorrows — stands on the highest eastern foothill, its beacon a cold, cyan flame.

The Grock Graveyard (The High Pass): In a hidden, high‑altitude valley near the central peaks lies the Grock Graveyard, where the greatest of the stone golems fell in the ancient war. It is rendered as a field of colossal, shattered stone limbs and heads, half‑buried in snow and shadow. A single, perfectly preserved Grock sits in a meditative pose, its eyes glowing with a faint, last flicker of holy gold, holding back a creeping tendril of shadow with its remaining hand.

The Northern Spur & The Southern Spur: The range extends to the top and bottom edges. In the far north, the mountains grow colder, their peaks merging into the icy frontiers of the Northern Vale. In the far south, the mountains descend into a dense, cursed thicket that bleeds into the Shadow Swamp of Azrya, marked by dying, twisted trees.

